4.43pm Through all the ranting about rain, we've successfully completed one innings in this match. Only 20 more, and we will have a result.
Expect Australia to come really, really hard at this target. They've done really well to close this innings out, but Bangladesh barely did themselves any favours. Could be argued that they might have been too watchful at the start, but this tame end vindicates that plan. They were up against a superior bowling line-up, but the platform had been laid. Two lose shots against Zampa undid all of that. Tamim Iqbal got more than thrice the next best batsman, and more than half of all his team. When that happens, you tend to have paltry totals. And 182 is a paltry total.
